688
01:01:37,396 --> 01:01:40,820
MY LIBERATION NOTES

689
01:01:40,903 --> 01:01:43,176
<i>I'm sorry. I didn't have time to ask you.</i>

690
01:01:43,921 --> 01:01:45,451
<i>What did he use to do?</i>

691
01:01:45,534 --> 01:01:47,519
<i>Maybe he's in hiding here.</i>

692
01:01:47,602 --> 01:01:50,745
-He bought alcohol again.
<i>-He says I should move there.</i>

693
01:01:50,828 --> 01:01:53,764
I'm a woman who has a lot of charm.

694
01:01:53,846 --> 01:01:55,336
You've got to be kidding me.

695
01:01:55,418 --> 01:01:58,851
<i>Is he on bad terms with his girlfriend?
Who has he been talking to for so long?</i>

696
01:01:58,933 --> 01:02:00,960
We're breaking up!
Just go out with her instead then!

697
01:02:01,042 --> 01:02:02,449
<i>Something I had to figure out</i>

698
01:02:02,531 --> 01:02:04,309
<i>but couldn't bring myself to.</i>

699
01:02:04,392 --> 01:02:06,667
<i>-What did Mr. Gu say to you?
-It's nothing.</i>

700
01:02:06,749 --> 01:02:08,900
<i>What? Yeom Mi-jeong doesn't live here.</i>

701
01:02:10,058 --> 01:02:12,952
<i>Don't tell me you went out with him.</i>

702
01:02:13,035 --> 01:02:14,359
I don't think I can do it.

703
01:02:14,441 --> 01:02:16,592
I want to feel whole for once.

704
01:02:17,129 --> 01:02:18,783
I'll pick it up later.

705
01:02:18,867 --> 01:02:20,479
<i>Why do you drink every day?</i>

706
01:02:21,182 --> 01:02:22,671
<i>Should I give you something
to do other than drink?</i>

